      "source": "CV",
      "text": "AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, Oracle Certified Java SE 7 Programmer (OCA), Mental Health First Aider",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "CV",
      "text": "University of South Wales — BSc (Hons) Computer Games Development, 2:1 (2012–2016)",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "CV",
      "text": "Let’s Connect: LinkedIn, GitHub, Dev Blog",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "Personal Biography",
      "text": "Parent of two. Partner for eleven years. Live near my parents after moving around a lot in my 20's.",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "CV",
      "text": "I cycle through these hobbies over the years: Hiking, Powerlifting, Mountain biking, Wargaming, Dungeons & Dragons (D&D), Miniature painting, Nail painting, Various side projects with technology",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "I have worked with Alex on multiple projects at Clinithink (Client). He is a positive and a hard working person making it a delight to work with him. At any given time he was available to help and also took feedback in a positive manner, solving the problem for success. He has a great pick up speed for technologies making it easier for us to start on new problems quickly and wrap them up. Communication is another great quality which helps understand and solve the problem easily for the product.",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "I worked with Alex for over 4 years and during that time he has grown from a software engineer through to a tech lead. Alex is extremely positive and is a real asset to any team. He has used his excellent interpersonal skills both with UK engineers as well as offshore engineers (India). Alex will try out any new technology and make a success of it. He changed from python to .Net during our time together and most recently has made huge strides with utilising AI as part of engineering practice through using Cursor. Alex's positivity, creativity and personality also provided significant input and support of the Wellness Team at Clinithink as well as the company wide internal comms team. His interpersonal skills also mean that he is interested, and I'd expect would flourish, in line management. We didn't manage to create the opportunity for Alex at Clinithink but I know he'll achieve this somewhere along his journey.",
      "author": "Phil Davies"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "I had the pleasure of working with Alex when he was the Tech Lead and I was the Product Manager. He has that rare combination of technical depth and pragmatic execution, always focused on delivering impact, unblocking the team, and just getting things done. Partnering with him made complex projects move faster and smoother, and I’d happily work with him again on any team.",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "Wow, it has been great working with Alex and watching him develop and grow in expertise. He is an expert coder who can turn his hand to any part of the software stack - backend, frontend, CI, design, test. He has become expert in handing some jobs over to an LLM. He doesn't just do the job as specified: he can see when there's an easier solution. He is quick to help others. He is collaborative, good humoured and hard working.",
      "author": "Thomas Guest"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "Alex is an excellent software engineer with outstanding technical skills who consistently delivers high-quality, production-ready code. His expertise in software development and problem-solving abilities make him an asset to any engineering team. He fearlessly voices his honest opinions and actively contributes innovative ideas that drive product advancement and elevate software quality across the team.",
      "author": "Peter Hatton"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "I've been very lucky to work with Alex on 3 different products. Massively impressive ability to grasp new tech, concepts and tooling to achieve our product goals. Alex is innovative - always finding ways to evolve and improve on how product features get built. He is efficient, quickly grasps what product - or anyone else - needs - and turns out quality code to boot. I wouldn't hesitate at the opportunity to work with Alex again and would highly recommend him to any future employer.",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "LinkedIn Recommendation",
      "text": "I worked with Alex for just over 3 years. I found him to be very flexible and versatile in his approach to work, and he has a broad-range of knowledge across the software landscape. Alex was always happy to help me with my technical problems; nothing was too much trouble for him.",
      "author": "Jean Rollinson"
    },
    {
      "id": "evidence-001",
      "source": "CV",
      "text": "Joined a small python/react team in a new domain. Python was rusty and I had never worked with django. I quickly got up to speed.",
      "author": "Alex Bainbridge"
    }
  ],
